cs.LG, cs.ST, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT. 

This paper deals with clustering algorithms and their application to correlated random variables. The use of k-means and spectral algorithms suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The analysis of different ways of measuring the dissimilarity of variables and the impact of diversity of initial points suggests a focus on statistical analysis, which falls under the category of cs.ST (Statistics). The use of similarity matrices and coefficients of determination suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and data mining, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of correlation matrices suggests a focus on information theory, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
